<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-05T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-05T17:00:00-05:00" n="644" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d644">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/2913: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Crane</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-05T18:00:00-04:00"><hi rend="italic">August 5,
                                            1920—6 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>200. Your No. 212, August 4, noon.</p>
                            <p>Unless representatives of Powers concerned are agreed on simultaneous
                                communication to the Chinese Government you should withhold
                                representations until further instructions.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>